This is, because you can't Java. How you will find out, where you use<p><pre><code>   first_names = [p.first_name for p in people]
</code></pre>
? More verbose, but right way in Java is like (you can do this better with enums and/or guava, it's just example):<p><pre><code>    class PersonTransformer implements Transformer {
        public Object transform(Object o) {
            return ((Person)o).getFirstName();
        }
    }
</code></pre>
and then:<p><pre><code>    Collection<String> firstNames = CollectionUtils.collect(people, new PersonTransformer());
</code></pre>
You can reuse it and, more important, you can search for it. Same for second example.
